    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>An Animal's Place</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Erin S Foster letter compares Michael Pollan's Nov 10 article about cruelty in factory farming to movie The Secret Life of Plants and contends people have to eat something; photo</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In high school, I was made to watch ''The Secret Life of Plants,'' a documentary (with a snappy Stevie Wonder soundtrack) based on the premise that even plant life is sentient: plants attached to an EKG-like machine showed erratic energy patterns when distressed. I can't wait for this film to make its inevitable DVD revival so I can watch the vegetarian hand-wringing. Surely we could be more humane to all living things, but don't we have to eat something?</p>
        <p>Erin E. Foster  Scarsdale, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
